org.reific.braid

Interface Braid

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BraidImpl

    public interface Braid

    Braid library provides transparent in-memory compression of java Strings, using a flyweight class Braid.

    A group of Braids is generally associated with a single Knot. The actual (normally compressed) data of the Braids is stored in the associated Knot.

    This javadoc content is also available on the ??? web page. All documentation is kept in javadocs because it guarantees consistency between what's on the web and what's in the source code. Also, it makes possible to access documentation straight from the IDE even if you work offline. This documentation pattern was inspired by the excellent mocking library Mockito
